{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Use event-driven (EventBus) pattern exclusively for all notifications, remove CallbackRegistry usage","detail":"EventBus is the right choice because: (1) it's already the primary pattern used by UserService and OrderService.createOrder, (2) it provides typed events, async handling, and an event log for debugging, (3) it enables loose coupling — new notification channels can subscribe without modifying existing services, (4) the package.json literally describes the system as having 'event-driven notifications'. The CallbackRegistry approach is simpler but creates tighter coupling and lacks event replay/logging.","tags":["architecture"],"scope":"src/services/notification.service.ts","agent_id":"agent-1","id":"01KMY9A2CPV83FPWEBESM08NVQ","timestamp":"2026-03-30T02:31:33.526Z"}
